<div id="review_2205639583" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2205639583" />
    <a title="Adam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29075798-adam"><img alt="Adam" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519711514p2/29075798.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2205639583?book_show_action=true">Apr 11, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Adam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Adam" href="/user/show/29075798-adam">Adam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audible Audio " href="/book/show/44864563-the-physician">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=story-5-star">story-5-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=narration-4-star">narration-4-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=read-2019">read-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=audible">audible</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=5-star-favorites">5-star-favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=long">long</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29075798-adam?shelf=favorites-2019">favorites-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2205639583" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10667433707449090462">Review of the audiobook narrated by Richard Higgins.<br/><br/>The Physician does what all great historical fiction accomplishes, which is bring you wholly to the place and time of the story. Not only that, but the cultural journey that Noah Gordon embarks on is the most fascinating of any book that I&apos;ve read before. The way that Gordon explores each culture through the lens of a 11th century traveler - especially the Jewish and Muslim cultures, which I wasn&apos;t familiar with - kept me completely captivated </span>
  <span id="freeText10667433707449090462" style="display:none">Review of the audiobook narrated by Richard Higgins.<br /><br />The Physician does what all great historical fiction accomplishes, which is bring you wholly to the place and time of the story. Not only that, but the cultural journey that Noah Gordon embarks on is the most fascinating of any book that I've read before. The way that Gordon explores each culture through the lens of a 11th century traveler - especially the Jewish and Muslim cultures, which I wasn't familiar with - kept me completely captivated from start to finish. That was important because nearly all of the secondary characters never grabbed me, and I typically don't enjoy books where I don't love the characters.<br /><br />Along the way Gordon gives us an insightful view into how early medieval preconceptions and religious beliefs contributed to the lack of advancement in medicine during that time. Somehow Gordon manages to describe people, places, cultures and events in exquisite and vivid detail, yet he rarely dwells upon things which would drag down the plot. It's a long book that never feels long due to how well written it is. Highly recommended.<br /><br />Richard Higgins provides a somewhat inconsistent narration. He's great with pronunciations, accents and I though he did well giving each character a distinct voice. On the other hand he has a flat delivery which doesn't always express the emotions of a scene well. Despite my reservations, in the end he didn't end up taking away from my overall enjoyment of the book - which I loved and I expect will be in my top 5 at the end of the year.<br /><br />Final verdict: 5 star story, 4 star narration, 5 stars overall</span>
  <a data-text-id="10667433707449090462" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


