<div id="review_3306922241" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3306922241" />
    <a title="Klaus" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/83849229-klaus"><img alt="Klaus" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618916901p2/83849229.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3306922241?book_show_action=true">Apr 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Klaus" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Klaus" href="/user/show/83849229-klaus">Klaus</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/83849229-klaus?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3306922241" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9761083496192946718">Gordon‘s „Physician“ is perhaps the most famous roadmovie of Historic Fiction. We follow Rob Cole from England to India and back, from being a Christian to being a Jew and back, and ironically, he comes back as a physician trained by Arvicenna and is still at the outskirts of society. <br/><br/>It has friendship, love, and war, but most of all it’s an intriguing picture of societies of that time. We get an insight into Christian, Jewish, and Muslim culture, and also a basic course in juggling. <br/><br/>Other than </span>
  <span id="freeText9761083496192946718" style="display:none">Gordon‘s „Physician“ is perhaps the most famous roadmovie of Historic Fiction. We follow Rob Cole from England to India and back, from being a Christian to being a Jew and back, and ironically, he comes back as a physician trained by Arvicenna and is still at the outskirts of society. <br /><br />It has friendship, love, and war, but most of all it’s an intriguing picture of societies of that time. We get an insight into Christian, Jewish, and Muslim culture, and also a basic course in juggling. <br /><br />Other than many classics of Historic Fiction, the protagonist doesn’t get involved with high politics in this one. He’s got political friends for sure, but this one is focused on the lives of ordinary people and the extraordinary hunger for knowledge of Rob, who travels from London to Isfahan just to study under one of the most famous physicians of all time.<br /><br />It’s a grand tale about ordinary people, prejudice, and the hunger for knowledge - four stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9761083496192946718" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


